Interface ISeriesProcessor<A extends Comparable<A>,O extends Comparable<O>>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AverageCrossingTradingAgent, DummyTradingAgentExecution, EquityCurveProcessor, TradeStatsProcessor
public interface ISeriesProcessor<A extends Comparable<A>,O extends Comparable<O>>

A processor with one or several inputs series, and one output series. In general, processors will be able to process realtime event from the input series. Several processors can be stacked together by feeding a processor's output to another as input.

wire

void wire(Map<String,? extends ISeries<A,O,? extends ISeriesPoint<A,O>>> input,
          ISeriesAugmentable<Date,Double,ISeriesPoint<Date,Double>> output)
Wire the processor with its input and output series. Input and output are connected with the same methods, to signal to the processor that it is completely wired, and it can start processing.

Parameters:
input - a map of inputs, mapped by their tags
output - a writable series

unwire

void unwire()
Unwire the processor. After this method, the processor should be detached from the inputs and it should stop writing to the output series.
